{
  "texts": [
    "Given the behaviour of κ 2 at z * a, it is not hard to see thatlim z→z * a ∂Φ(z) ∼ 1 z -z * a,whilst β(z) has a simple zero and γ(z) a simple pole as z → z * a.",
    "We shall argue for this behaviour of ∂Φ(z) once again in section 5.1 but from an alternative perspective, relating ∂Φ(z) to operators that are conformal tensors.",
    "Nonetheless, the bosonization gives a clear way to see why zeroes in β are associated with poles in γ and ∂Φ.",
    "JHEP04(2024)048 Connections to the AdS 3 sigma modelIt is perhaps not surprising that the most natural spacetime interpretation for the theory is in terms of Wakimoto coordinates.",
    "Firstly, we have seen that the twistor geometry has a clean connection with spacetime in Wakimoto coordinates and the theory is a twistor string theory of a novel kind."
